    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-07T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-07T09:00:00-05:00" n="19"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.0012/538</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-07T16:00:00+02:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 7, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9:30 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>My telegram of September 7.<note n="1" xml:id="d19fn1">Not printed.</note> Your
                    telegram October 5, 2 p.m. Contents thereof concerning arbitration communicated
                    to the Foreign Office. Latter says on account of extra work due to the question
                    of capitulations they have been unable to give it desired attention but will do
                    so now.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
